::FZ::

"Impressive indeed," FZ replies as he looks over the prototypes. He didn't want to admit it, but Lady Hawk knew what she was doing.

He looks over at her. "How long untill they are ready? I believe I might have a mission for them..."




--- In nbwrpg@y..., "CYBERWOLF4" <cyberwolf4@p...> wrote:
> Lady Hawk scans her creations one more time before replying. "Thier growth
> rate increases each day. these samples are merely two days old and already a
> third of the way to thier estimated full size." The stasis field on the left
> held a scorpion alien about three feet tall, redish with mandables, half a
> claw on each hand, a tail about four feet long. It stood somewhat hunched on
> two feet, it's oblong head forward to maintain balance.
> 
> On the right a snake alien made from Najahs cobra DNA coiled about five feet
> tall. Its forked toung dripping deadly venom suitable for melting it's prey
> before digesting it. It uncoiled pushing itself to it's full length of
> aproximately fifteen feet. A dark green crossbread of it's serpentine scales
> and the aliens armored almost shelllike skin reflected the light of the
> room. It flexxed a hood about six feet in diameter. "An impresive sight if I
> may be so modest." Lady Hawk was torn by her accomplishment. She was
> fearfull for what these crossbreeds were to be used for, but she couldn't
> help to feel a small bit of pride based on the life she had just created.
